-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Derivation and third-party code
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

padMule is a port of aMule to iPadOS. The engine is a Rust rewrite (crates/), and
the native shell is SwiftUI (ios/). It derives from, and in places ports code
and on-disk/wire formats from:

  aMule 3.0.1
    Copyright (C) The aMule Team and contributors
    Licensed GPL-2.0-or-later.
    The upstream source is vendored, unmodified, under amule-3.0.1/ and serves as
    the reference oracle for this port. Its own license, authors, and credits are
    preserved there:
      amule-3.0.1/LICENSE.md      (GNU GPL v2)
      amule-3.0.1/docs/COPYING    (GNU GPL v2, identical to this repo's LICENSE)
      amule-3.0.1/docs/AUTHORS.md (the aMule Team)

  aMule itself descends from eMule (GPL-2.0-or-later, (C) the eMule Team). Where
  padMule follows eMule 0.50a as the wire/format authority, that too is GPL code.

Because padMule reuses and ports GPL-2.0-or-later code, padMule as a whole is
licensed GPL-2.0-or-later. Any file borrowed from aMule, eMule, or another fork
keeps its original copyright and license notices.
